# 1. １週間前

Musicians: Hey, have you guys heard the news?!
Musicians: What news...? Oh, are you talking about their event?
Musicians: Of course we heard! Everyone around here's been asking about it!
Musicians: Next week at COL, right? I can't wait to see what it's like...!
Locals: I wonder how their event's going to go. Rumor has it that An and the others are training pretty hard for it...
Locals: Surpassing RAD WEEKEND won't be easy... But after seeing An and Kohane battle that time... They proved themselves as incredible singers, so maybe, just maybe...
Ken: ...
Akito: Alright, we all done warming up?
An: Yeah, I'm ready to start whenever.
An: We only have one week remaining, so we gotta make the most of every second we have left.
An: Don't go easy on us, Dad.
Ken: Oh, I won't. Get ready to cling on for dear life.
Kohane: (Just one week to go...)
Kohane: (In one week's time, it's really happening.)
Kohane: (It felt like we had plenty of time to prepare when we first chose that date...)
Kohane: (But this is it...!)
Ken: I went to hear what the locals were saying yesterday...
Ken: The air was buzzing with anticipation.
Ken: Surpassing RAD WEEKEND meant having to get all our pieces on the board.
Ken: And now...
Ken: Akito, you ignited everyone's hearts.
Ken: Toya, you completed your song.
Ken: An, you got the locals behind you.
Ken: Kotaro, EVER... You guys found the courage to get back on your feet.
Ken: And last but not least, Kohane, you unlocked your potential.
Ken: It's now or never. Things have reached a fever pitch, so this is your best chance.
Kohane: ... Right!
An: We found people to staff our event too, so now we just gotta focus all our attention on the task at hand.
Toya: Yes, and we really don't have a second to waste.
Akito: Then, let's start preparing like we mean it for next week. Are you all ready?!
Everyone: Yeah! Yes! Okay!
Kohane: (It's really happening...)
Kohane: (Our moment!)
Kohane: Phew...
Kohane: (Everyone was much more motivated than usual during practice today.)
Kohane: (There was a nice tension in the air. But I'm exhausted after singing for hours and hours.)
Kohane: (Still, I am feeling a lot better now as a result...)
Kohane: (Just one week to go...)
Kohane: This is it...
???: <Kohane? Are you still awake?>
Kohane: Oh...!
Kohane: Hi, Miku. What brings you here so late?
Miku: <Sorry, I know you must be tired. But I wanted to talk to you.>
Kohane: Huh? To me?
Miku: <Yes. It's one week from today, right?>
Miku: <I guessed you might be feeling a little anxious, so I'm here to help you relax.>
Kohane: Oh...
Kohane: You really are incredible, Miku. You saw right through me.
Kohane: I can't seem to stay still. I mean, everything's coming to a head next week...
Miku: <Don't worry, Kohane.>
Kohane: Huh...?
Miku: <I'm sure you'll do just fine.>
Miku: <Because you've never once run away from your feelings.>
Kohane: Miku...
Kohane: Thanks, I really appreciate it...!
Kohane: (She's right... I was put to the test over and over along the way, but I'm standing here right now because I kept trying.)
Kohane: (I mean, I've overcome so much...!)
Ken: Go show them that you're just as passionate about what you're doing as we were.
An: Oh, I will!
Ken: Alright, that takes care of An's task... Which just leaves yours.
Kohane: ...! Right!
Kohane: (My task...)
Kohane: (What's he going to ask me to do? The others' tasks all sounded really hard.)
Ken: Let me start by saying...
Ken: You'll be tackling two.
Kohane: What...?
Toya: Two...?
Ken: That's right.
Ken: However, I'll only be telling you about one today. I'll tell you about the other after you've completed this one so that you can stay focused on the task at hand.
Kohane: U-Understood...!
Ken: Now, for your first task, you'll need to...
Ken: Become a powerful singer.
Kohane: Huh?
Ken: I'm not talking about just polishing your skills.
Ken: You need to be powerful enough to blast a hole in the moment RAD WEEKEND became a legend.
An: ...?!
Kohane: B-Blast a hole...?
